title: As coronavirus cases surge across the US, the debate over whether to require Americans to wear a mask to slow the spread of the virus has intensified
There are at least 3,286,025 US coronavirus cases
Trump and Fauci not speaking as coronavirus pandemic worsens
description: For months, amid the worst pandemic in a century, President Donald Trump insisted all was well between him and the nation's top infectious disease specialist.

title: Betsy DeVos is asked if she has a plan to reopen schools safely. Watch her response.
description: CNN's Dana Bash speaks to Education Secretary Besty DeVos about whether or not she has a plan for schools to safely reopen for students as Covid-19 cases surge in the US.

title: DeVos won't say if schools should follow CDC guidelines to reopen
description: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos on Sunday refused to say whether schools should follow guidelines from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention on reopening, saying those guidelines are meant to be "flexible."

title: How one of the largest school districts in the US is preparing for the start of the school year and what parents think about it
description: The signage reminding students to stay 6 feet apart is already on the floors. The plexiglass is up in the front office. The desks are spaced in a socially-distanced way in the classrooms.

title: ER doctor reacts to Trump's claim: It's a preposterous thought
description: An emergency room physician from Arizona, which saw a recent spike in coronavirus cases, discusses a claim made by President Trump that a majority of coronavirus patients "automatically get better."

title: First cases of coronavirus-related inflammatory syndrome identified in children in South Carolina
description: • Why Britons won't wear masks • Navajo Nation becomes a case study amid Arizona's Covid-19 spike • Florida smashes record for new virus cases

title: Lindsey Graham says he will ask Mueller to testify before Senate panel
description: • Mueller breaks his silence on Roger Stone • Romney calls Trump's act of clemency 'unprecedented, historic corruption'

title: An explosion on a naval ship in San Diego injures sailors and causes a three-alarm fire
description: Several sailors were injured after an explosion on board a ship at the US Naval Base in San Diego, according to the San Diego Fire Department (SDFD).

title: NYT: Trump considered selling Puerto Rico after Hurricane Maria, ex-Cabinet official says
description: President Donald Trump considered the idea of selling Puerto Rico in 2017 after the island was devastated by Hurricane Maria, the former acting Homeland Security secretary told The New York Times in an interview published Friday.

title: LA district attorney responds to being targeted by Black Lives Matter
description: Black Lives Matter is targeting the Black district attorney of L.A. County -- the first Black person ever to hold the office. They say Jackie Lacey refuses to prosecute officers who kill civilians; she says she is just following the law.

title: He flaunted jets and wads of cash to 2.5 million followers. Then Feds found his posts
description: Ramon Abbas openly flaunted a lavish lifestyle of private jets, designer clothes and luxury cars.

title: Trump attempts to justify his frequent golf outings as 'exercise'
description: President Donald Trump on Sunday defended what he described as his "exercise" regimen, tweeting a justification for his frequent golf outings and claiming them as sufficient physical activity.

title: Bollywood star, once dubbed 'The Most Beautiful Woman in the World,' tests positive for Covid-19
description: Iconic Bollywood actress Aishwarya Rai Bachchan and her daughter, Aaradhya, tested positive for coronavirus following news that Aishwarya's husband and father-in-law were hospitalized with the virus.

title: Brian Stelter: Big lies are taking their toll
description: CNN's Brian Stelter breaks down President Donald Trump's recent false and confusing claims.

title: Opinion: The truth Trump won't see about reopening schools
description: "Come on, it's not that hard." So said White House economic adviser Larry Kudlow to CNN's Kaitlan Collins on Friday when asked about lost productivity, as parents care for children out of school during the pandemic. "Just go back to school, we can do that."

title: Former USA Gymnastics coach is arrested and faces charges of lewdness with a minor
description: A former gymnastics coach was arrested in Las Vegas and faces 14 counts of lewdness with a child under age 14, authorities said

title: A massive fire has destroyed a 249-year-old church in California
description: California firefighters are investigating the origin of a fire that destroyed a historic 249-year-old Catholic church.

title: What August Alsina said after Jada Pinkett Smith and Will Smith's 'Red Table Talk'
description: People are fascinated by August Alsina's "entanglement" with Jada Pinkett Smith, but the singer seems less than thrilled with all the attention.

title: Italian Alps experiencing a colorful phenomenon
description: Scientists are studying the climate impact of the spread of algae that is turning snow pink in the Italian Alps.

title: Pope 'very saddened' as Turkey converts Hagia Sophia from museum to mosque
description: Pope Francis stood in silence for several minutes at his weekly Angelus prayer Sunday, after he talked about Turkey's decision to convert the Hagia Sophia back into a mosque.

title: Penguins take field trip to Chicago museum
description: Penguins from the Shedd Aquarium spent the day at the Field Museum checking out their ancestors, like the T. Rex.

title: Somebody paid a record $114,000 for a rare Super Mario Bros. video game
description: An anonymous buyer bid a record $114,000 for a rare, unopened copy of the classic video game Super Mario Bros.

title: USC to remove John Wayne exhibit after actor's racist comments resurfaced
description: The University of Southern California's School of Cinematic Arts will remove an exhibit dedicated to John Wayne as the late actor's past bigoted remarks have come under increased scrutiny.

title: Dramatic video shows 8-year-old trapped in flood
description: Rescue workers in Walton Hills, Ohio, respond to a call of an eight-year-old girl stranded in a flooded creek.

title: Teen surfer dies in suspected shark attack
description: A 15-year-old boy died in a suspected shark attack while surfing in New South Wales, Australia, police said Saturday.

title: Texas is a swing state in 2020, new polls reveal
description: New CBS News/YouGov polls show President Donald Trump is in trouble in three states he won in 2016. He's tied with former Vice President Joe Biden in Arizona (46% to 46%), a state he won by four points in 2016. Trump's down 48% to 42% in Florida, a state he took by a point in 2016.

title: Republican says he'd rather vote for a 'tuna fish sandwich' over Trump
description: Ads aren't unusual for an election year, but as CNN's Jeff Zeleny reports, Republican "Never Trump" groups are spending millions hoping to make the leader of their party a one-term president.

title: Analysis: Historians will likely rank Trump as one of the worst presidents
description: Poll of the week: A new Gallup poll puts President Donald Trump's approval rating at 38%. His disapproval rating stands at 57%.

title: Opinion: Trump is the anti-Lincoln
description: President Donald Trump is famously unencumbered by a sense of history -- except when he's trying to use American history as a wedge in the culture wars.

title: Analysis: Why the dumb mask debate isn't over
description: With just 114 days until the 2020 election, it will be here before you know it. Every Sunday, I will outline the 5 BIG storylines you need to know to understand the upcoming week on the campaign trail. And they're ranked -- so the No. 1 story is the most important of the coming week.

title: Hundreds of people celebrated July 4th at a Michigan lake. Now some have Covid-19
description: After revelers celebrated the Fourth of July at a Michigan lake, some started testing positive for Covid-19 -- prompting health officials to warn other party-goers that they might have be infected, too.

title: Opinion: The two reasons Covid-19 is getting worse in the US
description: The pandemic of 2020 is ravaging the United States faster every day. While many other developed countries gradually get back to normal, Americans are contracting Covid-19 in numbers that are hard to comprehend, breaking records every day.

title: 7 takeaways from Disney World's July reopening
description: I was one of the first guests back in Disney World on Saturday after nearly four months of the parks being closed down because of Covid-19.

title: Brooklyn Beckham and Nicola Peltz are getting married
description: Brooklyn Beckham asked Nicola Peltz to marry him, and she said yes, the cameraman and model announced on Saturday.

title: She took a dishwashing job at her husband's nursing home so she could visit him during the pandemic
description: Mary Daniel visited her husband Steve every day at his Florida memory care center until they stopped allowing visitors in March because of the coronavirus pandemic.

title: Watch police officer borrow bike to catch a murder suspect
description: A biker in Atlanta helped police catch a murder suspect by loaning one of the officers his bike for the chase.

title: Valentina Sampaio becomes Sports Illustrated's first trans model
description: She is no stranger to making history. In 2017 she became the first trans woman to appear on the cover of Vogue Paris. Two years later, she was the first openly transgender model to be hired by Victoria's Secret. Now in 2020, 23-year-old Valentina Sampaio continues to break barriers in the modeling industry by becoming the first trans woman to be featured by Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue.

title: 'Soda bombs' and 'pizza security': The lessons of making a car for Domino's
description: In 2012, Domino's enlisted the automaker Local Motors, where Nicholas de Peyer worked, to reinvent pizza delivery. He spent the next 18 months obsessed with making the ultimate pizza delivery car, and by the end of it, discovered that the best solution wasn't about the pizza.

title: Get ready for an awful earnings season
description: Major companies are about to tell investors how they fared during the second quarter as the coronavirus swept over America. And there's no sugarcoating it. To paraphrase the title of a popular children's book: It was a terrible, horrible, no good, very bad three months.

title: Workers demanding union rights plan to walk off the job in nationwide Strike for Black Lives
description: A coalition of Black advocacy groups and labor activists are organizing a nationwide strike to pressure corporations, such as McDonald's, Amazon, Uber and Lyft, to raise wages and allow their workers to form unions.

title: Goya's galling affront to Latinos
description: Like most of my friends and family I have Goya products in my cupboard. Adobo, Sazón with Coriander and Anatto, Sofrito (Tomato, though sometimes I'll get the Recaito Cilantro, and black and pink beans.)

title: What a new 'Wonder Years' could offer America
description: I had my own "wonder years" -- and I bet most of you did, too. The emotional connections triggered by ABC's "The Wonder Years" throughout its five-year run (1988-93) were so deeply familiar to those of us who grew up in the 1960s, or even earlier, that it didn't seem to matter that it focused on a White middle-class family on Long Island when Lyndon Johnson's presidency gave way to Richard Nixon's -- even if that setting felt out of step with our lived experience in real life.

title: Why Taiwan got it right on Covid (and the US didn't)
description: Public health professionals around the world have lauded Taiwan's response to the coronavirus pandemic. Along with nearby countries such as South Korea and Singapore, Taiwan has employed policy responses to Covid-19 that are worthy of emulation around the world. Taiwan, in particular, effectively contained Covid-19 by springing to action early, coordinating a government-wide response to the virus, and clearly communicating with its citizenry.

title: Pro sports starting vast, science-based experiment in Covid re-entry
description: The surge of Covid-19 cases in the South and Southwest has demonstrated the tragic consequences of a deliberately uninformed, poorly coordinated response to the pandemic.

title: I teach public school. I don't want to die
description: I am a public school teacher and I don't want to die. As the question of whether and how to reopen schools in the fall intensifies, with parents and especially politicians expressing their opinions, I want to ask: Has anyone asked what we want to do in the fall?

title: How to decide who gets the Covid-19 vaccine first
description: Last month, Moderna Health announced advancements in Covid-19 vaccine trials, prompting speculation that a vaccine might be available as early as next year. But with this increased optimism comes challenges in manufacturing and distribution. Vaccines take time to produce, and the initial supply might not meet US demands. As the race for a Covid-19 vaccine heats up, policymakers must confront a series of pressing questions: Who should get the vaccine first, and how should that decision be made?

title: What's behind Roberts' stinging rebuke of Trump
description: With Thursday's decisions rejecting President Donald Trump's absolutist legal claim that he stands above the law, Chief Justice John Roberts put the finishing touch on a remarkable Supreme Court term defined by his transformation into a powerful voice of judicial independence -- or, at least, unpredictability.

title: Refi rates at 2.53% APR (15 yr). Do you qualify?
Pay 0% interest until 2021 with a better card
This may be the big winner of the market crash
Duda declares victory in Poland's presidential race, rival says too close to call
description: Poland's incumbent President Andrzej Duda declared victory in the country's presidential election Sunday, but his opponent refused to accept defeat, saying exit polls show the election is still too close to call.

title: Five killed in siege at South African church
description: Five people were killed in a siege at a church in South Africa on Saturday, police said.

title: How Cuba has managed to flatten the curve
description: More than 121,000 people have died from coronavirus in the Caribbean and South America, but as CNN's Patrick Oppmann reports, the island nation of Cuba has managed to flatten the curve.

title: Japan to build one of the world's most sophisticated stealth jet fighters
Man accused of killing eight police officers dies in shootout while trying to flee custody
description: A man accused of killing eight police officers in India was shot dead Friday while allegedly trying to flee custody after his arrest, authorities said.

title: Pathologist found blood clots in 'almost every organ' during autopsies on Covid-19 patients
description: Autopsies on people who died of the coronavirus are helping doctors understand how the disease affects the body -- and one of the most remarkable findings concerned blood clotting, a pathologist says.

title: This guitar-playing skateboarder is warming hearts in pandemic-stricken Atlanta
description: One of the bright spots in Atlanta as it struggles under the weight of the coronavirus pandemic is Chavis Flagg, a guitar player who has turned the city's popular Beltline trail into his stage.

title: 5 people were shot during a dispute at a Michigan apartment complex
description: An altercation at a Michigan apartment complex ended with five people shot Sunday morning, Lansing Police Chief Daryl Green said.

title: After nearly 110 years of naval aviation, the US Navy has welcomed its first Black female tactical jet pilot
description: Soaring through the glass ceilings of both her gender and race, Lt. j.g. Madeline Swegle has made history as the US Navy's first Black female tactical aircraft pilot.

title: Understanding the dress codes of Orthodox Jewish women
description: Based on the true story of Deborah Feldman, a Jewish woman who left the Satmar community in Williamsburg, Brooklyn in search of a new life, the hit Netflix series "Unorthodox" has brought Hasidic culture -- and its female dress codes -- into mainstream focus. One of the most talked about aspects of the show is the clothing, which shapes lead character Esty's (played by Shira Haas) story from beginning to end.

title: In Russia, drawing a woman's body can get you arrested
description: Yulia Tsvetkova is unsure about her future. She has been criminally charged with the "production and dissemination of pornographic materials," after sharing stylized depictions of vaginas on social media. The resident of a remote city in Russia's Far East, she was released from house arrest on March 16 after four months, but is still under strict travel restrictions and faces up to six years in jail.

title: The one item in every genius' closet
description: When the disgraced health entrepreneur Elizabeth Holmes was indicted on fraud charges for her lab-testing company Theranos last year, much of the media discussion rested not on her alleged corporate recklessness and staggering abuses of trust, but on her sartorial choices: black jackets, black slacks, and -- most importantly -- black turtlenecks.

title: Artists skytype over ICE detention centers
description: This Independence Day Weekend, 80 artists are asking Americans to look up at the skies. Over July 3 and 4, messages related to immigration will be written at 10,000 feet by World War II military planes, sky-typed over 80 sites related to the country's network of US Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) detention facilities, immigration courts, and the southern border. The idea is to bring attention to these facilities, which may not be familiar to many Americans.

title: Photos capture the magic of everyday life in America
description: When photographer William Eggleston arrived in Manhattan in 1967, he brought a suitcase filled with color slides and prints taken around the Mississippi Delta. They were scenes of the low-slung homes, blue skies, flat lands, and ordinary people of the American South -- all rendered in what would eventually become his iconic high-chroma, saturated hues.

title: The drama that changed TV history 30 years ago
description: Before Netflix, before sagas like "Game of Thrones" -- before high-speed internet -- there was "Twin Peaks."

title: Halle Berry and the erasure of Black trans people in Hollywood
description: Representation in Hollywood isn't just about race.

title: 'Palm Springs' like 'Groundhog Day' again
description: Andy Samberg becomes the latest "Saturday Night Live" alum to explore movie stardom with "Palm Springs," a romantic comedy co-starring Cristin Milioti. If that career arc sounds familiar, so does most everything about this breezy "Groundhog Day"-esque premise, which casts Samberg as a guy repeating the same day over and over.
